# FAQ Page
msgid "faq.page_title"
msgstr "Frequently Asked Questions"

msgid "faq.page_description"
msgstr "Find answers to common questions about our platform"

msgid "faq.title"
msgstr "Frequently Asked Questions"

msgid "faq.intro"
msgstr "Find answers to common questions about our platform, SDG classification, ORCID integration, and more."

msgid "faq.section.general"
msgstr "General Questions"

msgid "faq.q1"
msgstr "What is this platform?"

msgid "faq.a1"
msgstr "This platform helps researchers and journals classify their publications according to the UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). We use advanced AI to analyze research content and automatically assign relevant SDG categories."

msgid "faq.q2"
msgstr "Who can use this platform?"

msgid "faq.a2"
msgstr "The platform is designed for researchers, academic institutions, journal publishers, and anyone interested in understanding how research contributes to the SDGs."

msgid "faq.q3"
msgstr "Is the service free?"

msgid "faq.a3"
msgstr "Yes, we offer a free tier for individual researchers. Premium features are available for institutions and publishers with high-volume needs."

msgid "faq.section.sdg"
msgstr "SDG Classification"

msgid "faq.q4"
msgstr "What are the SDGs?"

msgid "faq.a4"
msgstr "The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) are 17 global goals set by the United Nations to achieve a better and more sustainable future for all. They address challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, and peace."

msgid "faq.q5"
msgstr "How accurate is the SDG classification?"

msgid "faq.a5"
msgstr "Our AI model achieves over 90% accuracy in SDG classification, validated against manually curated datasets. The system continuously learns and improves from feedback."

msgid "faq.q6"
msgstr "Can I classify multiple papers at once?"

msgid "faq.a6"
msgstr "Yes, premium users can upload batches of PDFs or submit multiple URLs for bulk classification. Contact us for institutional plans."

msgid "faq.section.orcid"
msgstr "ORCID Integration"

msgid "faq.q7"
msgstr "What is ORCID?"

msgid "faq.a7"
msgstr "ORCID (Open Researcher and Contributor ID) provides a persistent digital identifier that distinguishes you from every other researcher. It supports automated linkages between you and your professional activities."

msgid "faq.q8"
msgstr "How do I connect my ORCID?"

msgid "faq.a8"
msgstr "You can link your ORCID during registration or later in your profile settings. This allows automatic import of your publications and ensures proper attribution."

msgid "faq.section.submission"
msgstr "Submission & Analysis"

msgid "faq.q9"
msgstr "How do I submit a paper for analysis?"

msgid "faq.a9"
msgstr "You can submit papers by uploading PDF files directly or providing DOI/URL links. The system will analyze the content and return SDG classifications within seconds."

msgid "faq.q10"
msgstr "What format do results come in?"

msgid "faq.a10"
msgstr "Results include SDG category assignments with confidence scores, visual badges for display, detailed reports, and exportable data in JSON or CSV formats."

msgid "faq.section.contact"
msgstr "Still Have Questions?"

msgid "faq.contact_info"
msgstr "Contact our support team at support@example.com or visit our contact page for assistance."
